name: 17 - Lesson 3 - KaiwaBun 2.mp3
format: mp3
duration: 01:13.352
id: 9de21047-9eb6-4fc1-be7d-89481f043672
subtitles:
  - id: 2e620f5b-217d-432b-8311-2bdea7d6baa5
    type: External
    chunksMetadata:
      count: 31
      endCue: 3596.8
    name: 17 - Lesson 3 - KaiwaBun 2.srt
clips:
  - id: b9f188d6-65d9-4669-ac1d-e1e3619810ed
    start: 00:05.38
    end: 00:26.46
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        ねえ、うちも留守番電話にしましょうよ。
        どうして。
        うち、共働きだから、昼間は留守が多いでしょ？
        うん。
        友達が、「オタクはいつも留守 ね 」って怒るのよ。
        夜、電話してくださいって言ったら？
        でも、夜は電話が来ても、出られないことが多いのよ。お風呂に入っていたりして…。
      meaning: |-
        
        Wife: Honey, shouldn't we start thinking about buying an answering machine?
        Husband: Why?
        Wife: Well, both working, and hardly ever home during the daytime.
        Husband: Hmm.
        Wife: My friends keep complaining that nobody answers the phone.
        Husband: If that happens, just ask them to call back in the evening.
        Wife: Its often impossible to pick up the phone at night. Such as when I'm in the tub.
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 03bd6413-159e-4926-83b1-d471103f31ec
    start: 00:27.72
    end: 00:36.32
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        テレビで面白いドラマやってるとき、電話に出ると、話がわからなくなるし…。
        そうだね。
        だから、留守番電話がいいと思うけど。
      meaning: |-
        Wife: When I pick up the phone during a good TV drama, it's easy to lose track of the story.
        Husband: True
        Wife: That's why I think we should buy an answering machine.
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: ecfbcd41-03c9-4108-a163-afa61017fc1d
    start: 00:36.84
    end: 00:50.0
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        でも、人に電話したとき、録音テープの声が聞こえるのは、いやだな。
        そう。
        ピーっていう音を聞いて、急いで録音するんだろう？
        ええ、そうよ。
        アナウンサー じゃないんだから。
      meaning: |-
        Husband: But I can't stand listening to a recording when I'm trying to reach somebody.
        Wife: Oh?
        Husband: When you hear the beep, don't you feel rushed to get everything on tape?
        Wife: Yes, of course.
        Husband: I'm not a professional announcer. I hate feeling like I'm talking into a microphone.
        Wife: Honey, if we bought an answering machine, the people calling us would talk into the tape. Not you and I.
        Husband: Maybe so, but I'm not going to force somebody to do something I dislike.
        Wife: I see. We'll just drop the whole idea, if that's the way you feel.
        Husband: Really? You're not unhappy?
        Wife: Not at all. I'll just refuse to do overtime at work, and come home early. We'll earn less money, of course.
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 3e33d7ff-e95a-4df1-a697-a7aa0b277173
    start: 00:50.24
    end: 01:02.78
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        マイクに向かって話すのは嫌だよ。
        でも、家が留守番電話にしたら、録音をするのは他の人よ。私たちが 録音するんじゃないのよ。
        自分がしたくないことは他の人にもさせたくないよ。
      meaning: |-
        I hate feeling like I'm talking into a microphone.
        Wife: Honey, if we bought an answering machine, the people calling us would talk into the tape. Not you and I.
        Husband: Maybe so, but I'm not going to force somebody to do something I dislike.
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: a3ddb162-23c2-4b51-a99a-dcd409c47e16
    start: 01:03.1
    end: 01:12.34
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        ああ、そう。
        じゃあ 留守番電話はやめましょう。
        いいの？
        ええ。残業を断って、早く家に帰るわ、収入は減るけど。
      meaning: |-
        Wife: I see. We'll just drop the whole idea, if that's the way you feel.
        Husband: Really? You're not unhappy?
        Wife: Not at all. I'll just refuse to do overtime at work, and come home early. We'll earn less money, of course.
    tags:
      - iij03
