name: 14 - Lesson 6 - Main Text.mp3
format: mp3
duration: 01:57.185
id: 3a770551-efd0-4ee0-b46c-7106a50e0467
clips:
  - id: 196cbd6c-c0cd-4ad5-aa82-ff4cd387acde
    start: 00:07.12
    end: 00:15.86
    fields:
      transcription: 社会人のための学校にも、いろいろなものがある。会社が社員の再教育のために学校を作る場合もある。
      meaning: There are many types of schools for adults. In some instances, companies will establish a school for re-educating employees.
    tags:
      - iij06
  - id: c9e6b4d0-57ff-4b24-9487-35f42e9ef1aa
    start: 00:16.26
    end: 00:29.12
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        会社の事業を大きくしたい場合には、社員を教育する必要がある。
        例えば海外の事業を盛んにするために、社員に語学教育を行う場合も多い。
      meaning: |-
        Companies must often educate workers in order to expand a business project.
        To enhance the prosperity of a foreign venture, for example, many companies give language training to their employees.
    tags:
      - iij06
  - id: 987c608c-04bb-4c77-8e40-c82f9800ffb1
    start: 00:29.62
    end: 00:35.46
    fields:
      transcription: 多くの情報を処理するため、社員にパソコンの操作を教えることもある。
      meaning: To cope with large volumes of information, some companies train their workers in the handling of computers.
    tags:
      - iij06
  - id: 650f1054-0bc5-48b8-b037-0a54b5605455
    start: 00:36.0
    end: 00:54.3
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        ある建設会社が社員のために作った教育機関の話を聞いた。
        これまでは現場で上司が指導していたが、上司も忙しくなってあまり指導ができなくなった。
        そこで社員教育のための学校を作ったのだそうである。
      meaning: |-
        At an education institute of a certain construction company, according to one report...
        Up until now, supervisors trained employees on the job. The supervisors' workloads increased, however, making continued training impossible.
        This prompted the company to start a school for training its employees.
    tags:
      - iij06
  - id: 14e638ea-c496-4f75-a507-af929133142d
    start: 00:54.78
    end: 01:11.12
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        授業は月曜から土曜まで、毎日朝九時から五時まで七時間。
        学費は無料で、会社から給料をもらう。夏休みもある。
        全員が寮に住む。寮は一人一部屋。
      meaning: |-
        Classes are held from Mondays through Saturdays. They start at nine in the morning and continue till five, for a total of seven hours a day.
        Tuition is free, and employees receive a salary from the company—as well as a summer break.
        All students live in a dormitory and are assigned separate rooms.
    tags:
      - iij06
  - id: beb24d7a-759e-47c8-9908-273dbf1bc20f
    start: 01:11.3
    end: 01:20.38
    fields:
      transcription: 一年間約千八百時間勉強したあと、現場で仕事を始め、三年か五年ぐらいで現場監督になる。
      meaning: At the end of a year consisting of 1,800 hours of study, employees go to work—where, in the space of three to five years, they are promoted to the rank of construction supervisor.
    tags:
      - iij06
  - id: 16030c1c-748a-4f4f-8e20-c6439db7d7e7
    start: 01:20.98
    end: 01:36.08
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        現在二十四名の学生がいるが、大学で建築を学んだ人は二名だけで、あとは商業などを学んだ人である。
        だから全くの初歩から建築の技術を習うことになる。
      meaning: |-
        At present, 24 students are enrolled in the school. Of this number, only two studied construction in college.
        The remainder majored in subjects like business, meaning they started learning about construction tech- niques from square one.
    tags:
      - iij06
  - id: 3fcc644f-7d59-47db-9aa7-6c4fecd49873
    start: 01:36.34
    end: 01:45.06
    fields:
      transcription: その学生の一人がこういった。「給料をもらいながら勉強しているので、しっかりやらなければいけないと感じています。」
      meaning: "\"We're getting paid as we learn,\" relates one student, \"and this makes everybody feel a need to study hard.\""
    tags:
      - iij06
  - id: cc903c41-aa8a-47a8-a251-dbb7d13357a9
    start: 01:45.44
    end: 01:56.4
    fields:
      transcription: 最近の学生はあまり勉強しないという人もいるが、もし学生が皆給料をもらうようになったら、よく勉強するようになるかもしれない。
      meaning: Many people criticize today's students for their reluctance to apply themselves to their studies. Perhaps they'd study harder, though, if they were all given a salary.
    tags:
      - iij06
